  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2025-07-23",
    "date": "2026-06-15T20:19:00Z",
    "text": "Newborn Screening Saves Lives Reauthorization Act of 2025\n\nThis bill reauthorizes through FY2030 and revises several programs and activities relating to newborn screening for certain conditions and diseases.\n\nAmong its changes, the bill reauthorizes and makes mandatory\n\nthe Hunter Kelly Research Program at the National Institutes of Health, andnational surveillance activities conducted by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.The bill also provides statutory authority for current regulations that exempt federally funded research on non-identified newborn blood spots (i.e., residual blood samples used to screen for serious conditions) from regulations that govern research on human subjects."
  },
